==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μέθοδος]]''' (''methodos'') "pursuit of knowledge, investigation, mode of prosecuting such inquiry, system", from '''[[μετά]]''', '''[[μέθ-]]''' (''metα'', 
''meth-'') "in the midst of, among, between, in common, along with, by aid of" + '''[[οδός]]''' (''odos'') "way, motion, journey".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-method.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A [[process]] by which a [[task]] is [[completed]]; a [[routine]].
#The [[study]] of a specific [[field]] of [[inquiry]]
#a type of [[theatrical]] acting wherein the '''method''' actor utilizes his personal [[emotion]]s from personal experience to [[portray]] a scripted [[scene]] 

